01/07/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia - - A mass grave from WWII has been discovered in Zagreb's outskirts, local media reported on Wednesday (June 30th). 
Forensic experts are investigating the site, believed to contain the remains of 17 people, likely Croatian and German soldiers killed by Yugoslav Communists at the end of the war. 
(Vecernji List, Nacional, DPA - 30/06/10)
